There in lies the cause of the animosity between myself and Blood Cult and the fundamental difference in approach to the game.  That's why I am not in BC now and that's why i'm not 'in-sync' with the membership of Blood Cult.<br>
<br>
I don't care what gear you have, uberness for me is attitude and personality - greatness is not in gear.  If it was then we'd probably all be speaking Egyptian or Mandarin.<br>
<br>
I am uber, not because of my gear, but because I realise I was wrong and I am brave enough to admit it. Now my question is how uber are you?  Or does the fact that I am - to quote an officer at the time of my BC departure 'politically sacrificial' meen that kicking me again is what you see as the 'uber' thing to do now?<br>
<br>
Mock me, go ahead and mock me, it will demonstrate that your opinion of great people is totaly based upon what they do in the game, and nothing at all to do with their actions.<br>
<br>
They will of course, because they'll never bring themselves to admit they where wrong, and for as long as they have a better breastplate, that is all that really matters.<br>
<br>
 <p>Venerable Pneumatic Dryll <br>
